# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Initially question is little confusing. But idea is simple remove the element asked in variable `val` and place another varible suppose `k` which is not equal to `val` i.e. `k != val` in it's position and return the count of k in array.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Once you understand the question, approach become simple 
Just take any variable to count all `k` in array. Then one by iterate through each element of array and skip the element equal to `val` and place the element `!= val` in it's place and increase the count. Finally return the count.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n)
- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

