# Approach
The loop goes through the vector checking each value against the restricted value `val`, for each value that is not `val` it will be set to the seperate index k which starts at the beginning of the vector overwriting the already checked values.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$O(n)$

- Space complexity:
$O(1)$

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int removeElement(vector<int>& nums, int val) {
        int k {};
        for(int i {}; i<nums.size();i++){
                (nums[i]!=val) ? nums[k++]=nums[i]:NULL;
        }
        return k;
    }
};
```

