public int ladderLength(String beginWord, String endWord, List<String> wordList) {
        /*Intuition : BFS traversal where each node is a word. 
        Start with beginWord node, and goal is to end on endWord.
        I am using a queue for BFS traversal.

        In order to go from beingWord to endWord, we need a morphing strategy. 
        We can either morph the beginWord with wordList as the reference, or
        we can use the english alphabets as guide/reference to explore all
        the different morphings. The latter performs well even in worst case,
        so I am adopting the latter foy my solution.

        Basically, we start with beginWord, explore all 1 transformation words,
        and if it matches the endWord we level up and return.
        Else, if any of the transformations exists in the wordList, we add it to 
        the queue for subsequent exploration, and remove it from the wordList to
        avoid revisiting the same node twice.*/
        Queue<String> q = new LinkedList<>();
        int level = 0;
        q.offer(beginWord);
        while(!q.isEmpty()){//O(wordList.length())
            char[] word = q.poll().toCharArray();
            for(int i=0; i<word.length; i++){//O(word.length)
                for(char c='a'; c<='z'; c++){//O(25)
                    char[] w = Arrays.copyOf(word, word.length);
                    w[i] = c;
                    String str = new String(w);
                    if(str.equals(endWord) && wordList.contains(str)) return level;
                    if(wordList.contains(str)){
                        q.offer(str);
                        wordList.remove(str);
                        level +=1;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return 0;
    }

